Description:
Quiet Street, Moments from Sydney Road
This eminently liveable Coburg home, walking distance to cafes, restaurants and specialty stores, with easily accessed transport, presents the perfect opportunity to refurbish, renovate or, STCA, redevelop. Currently comprising two bedrooms, central bathroom, kitchen offering stainless steel Smeg appliances and dishwasher, dining room with split system heating and cooling and separate lounge room.
Brilliant inner-city 499sqm lot in the heart of Coburg
Close to cafes, restaurants and specialty retail stores
Off-street parking
Ideal opportunity to refurbish, renovate or redevelop (STCA)
Tidy and liveable Californian Bungalow, easy to lease.
Outside, a sheltered paved area, external second toilet, large lock-up single garage, smaller garden shed, outside trough and two room bungalow with laundry and additional shower facilities. Create the perfect inner city lifestyle or ideal investment property.

Description:
Stylish Modern Living
Stunning Lifestyle Opportunity. This sensational new residence offers the very best in low maintenance living with a functional floor plan and the highest quality fittings throughout. Located near public transport, offering direct access into the CBD.On land of 250 sqms approx. this new home has a generous front yard, and grand entrance into the open plan living, meals and stylish kitchen, complete with ultra-glaze cabinetry with soft closing drawers, 80mm striking caesar stone benchtops. 600mm S/S appliances including dishwasher and double under bench kitchen sink with black chrome LED mixer tapware. Breakfast bench with pendant lighting, LED strip lighting above cooktop and finished with tasmanian oak timber flooring. Other features include three generous bedrooms, master with walk-in robe, ensuite with floor to ceiling porcelain tiles and balcony, the other bedrooms have built in robes. The main central bathroom offers 1200mmm shower and black chrome fittings, single vanity with above counter basin, combined toilet, fan and floor to ceiling porcelain tiles. The downstairs powder room and laundry are next to each other. Other highlights include, heating and cooling throughout , secure front yard, rear court yard, alarm system and intercom, single remote garage with rear and internal access plus driveway space for 2nd car. Close to Nicholson Street tram into the CBD plus surrounding parklands, and local shopping precincts.
Insights: 2 Elizabeth Street, Coburg VIC 3058 was last sold in 2019 and 146 other 3 bedroom house in Coburg have recently been sold.

Description:
Sold - $385,000
Featuring a northerly courtyard and front position, this sunlit one bedroom villa combines home comforts with an amazing location so close to Coburg's best features. Open plan with a sunny kitchen, highlighting a gas cooktop, canopy rangehood, great storage and counter space, the design flows in one direction to a living room and outside to the sizeable private courtyard. Adjoining the bedroom is a combined bathroom/laundry, and a hatch in the bedroom ceiling reveals extensive storage space. Extras include heating/cooling, timber flooring and carport parking, and the instantly liveable home could become a beauty with smart enhancement. Within a stroll of Coburg Train Station, parks, trams, cafes, restaurants, Coburg Market, bike paths and more, this is definitely one to take a close look at.

The Champ Is Here!

Description:
Edwardian Charm, Family Appeal
Charismatic, comfortable and recently renovated this generously proportioned three bedroom Edwardian family home boasts a large north-facing backyard, with coveted rear right-of-way access.
Situated along a wide streetscape, surrounded by charming period homes and wonderful family orientated amenities, this attractive property also offers potential to add your own touches.
Inside, high ceilings and decorative cornices are featured throughout a wide central hallway and large lounge area with brand new carpet.
Bathed in northerly light, a fully renovated kitchen/meals will impress with modern stainless steel electric appliances, bench tops, glass splashbacks, large pantry and abundant soft-close cabinetry.
Spacious accommodation comprises three delightful bedrooms with high ceilings, decorative plasterwork and plush, modern carpet underfoot.
Immediately comfortable, the home has an updated main bathroom, with shower over a bath and vanity, along with separate laundry, toilet, modern floorboards, new carpet, gas heater and storage sheds.
Metres from Bush Reserve parklands, tennis and bowls clubs and Bell Street buses, while cosmopolitan Sydney Road shops, cafes, Coburg Market, Coburg West primary, Coburg High school, Coburg North Village, trains and trams are all within easy reach.
Insights: 90 Victoria Street, Coburg VIC 3058 was last sold in 2019 and 146 other 3 bedroom house in Coburg have recently been sold.

High, Safe And Secure

An outstanding Coburg landmark development. An architects paradise with luxury fit and finishes. Secure, high and safe. Enjoy the views, you can see for miles.

Premium fixtures, beautiful bamboo flooring. Open plan living and dining, two (2) good size bedrooms (with built-in robes). Main bedroom with ensuite. Three balconies. This is a home for an entertainer. The kitchen includes: Smeg appliances including dishwasher, integrated fridge and a 40mm caesarstone bench top.
The Basics:
* Bamboo floors

* Undercover allocated parking space

Description:
Eye To An Exciting Future
Defined by soaring ceilings, natural light and generous design, this double fronted three bedroom period home boasts an optimal northerly rear aspect and a substantial block of approximately 542m2. Comprising a living room, large adjoining kitchen/dining, covered outdoor area and bungalow, the well kept abode is comfortable right now and ready for a new buyer to bring their vision to life and really make themselves at home. An oversized gas cooktop, electric oven, canopy rangehood, good work space and plenty of cupboards equip the kitchen and there's a built-in barbecue outdoors. Three double bedrooms share a large sparkling bathroom, ducted heating teams with an air conditioner and security system in enhancing comfort throughout the seasons, there's a garden shed for storage and a long side driveway and deep garage take care of parking. There's lots to love about the vibrant locale too: everything from buzzing Coburg Market to Sydney Road trams, trains, buses, Coburg Lake Reserve and schools is within a stroll.

Description:
Healthy, Efficient, Stylish
Located in a prime location opposite newly built coburg north primary school, Montessori pre-school, Harmony Park and a short walk to the new Coles concept store, shops , transport , amenities and airports. This home is designed and built for healthy living whilst achieving energy efficiency , style and low maintenance living. Features a unique air filtration and transfer system to maintain fresher, cleaner air quality. Also the architectural finishes are designed to minimise dust collection and filtered water to showers, bath as well as RO alkaline drinking and cooking water. The edible organic gardens provide for fresh seasonal produce to work and maintain with ease. With 3 large bedrooms, 3 brilliant kitchens that include induction and gas cooktops, double ovens, combi oven, integrated dishwasher and a commercial pizza bakery and integrated BBQ with wok burner, sink and rangehood. 2 bathrooms and laundries, huge living areas and double garage. Features Bosch hydronic heating, air conditioning to all rooms, continuous Bosch hot water service and beautiful polished porcelain and concrete floors. Newly completed and built to last , this property is often sought but rarely found.

Description:
High, Safe And Secure
The Living:
An outstanding Coburg landmark development. An architects paradise with luxury fit and finishes. Secure, high and safe. Enjoy the views, you can see for miles.

Premium fixtures, beautiful bamboo flooring. Open plan living and dining, two (2) good size bedrooms (with built-in robes). Main bedroom with ensuite. Three balconies. This is a home for an entertainer. The kitchen includes: Smeg appliances including dishwasher, integrated fridge and a 40mm caesarstone bench top.
The Basics:
* Bamboo floors
* Smeg stainless steel cooking appliances
* Stainless steel dishwasher
* Ample storage space
* Reverse cycle split system
* Undercover allocated parking space
* Storage cage

* Landmark Coburg complex
The Locale:
Trams and trains at your doorstep. Close to primary and secondary schools. A short walk to Sydney Road cafes, restaurants and shopping precinct.

Description:
Comfort and charm in leafy surrounds
This charming and immaculately maintained four bedroom weatherboard sits in a quiet and leafy Coburg street just moments from the bustling Sydney Road shopping strip, as well as trams, trains, parks and schools. With hardwood floors throughout, this stunning residence boasts four generously sized bedrooms including a huge master with BIRs. The spacious and light filled open plan kitchen, dining and living area offers a versatile and comfortable space for family meals, entertaining and relaxing alike. The large paved backyard is perfect for outdoor dining and entertaining and the self-contained unit at the back comes equipped with a large living space and functional and spacious kitchen. Other features include a spacious laundry with a second toilet and extra storage, heating and cooling throughout the house and generous off street parking. Just waiting to be embraced this house offers distinctive character and immediate liveability in a remarkable area.

Description:
Low Maintenance Living in a Prime Locale
SALE BY SET DATE Closing Tuesday 16th April at 6pm
Neighboring the picturesque Merri Creek park lands, this superbly located two bedroom villa delivers exceptional lifestyle choices. Enjoy your tranquil surrounds, whilst Nicholson Street trams and buses ensure swift passage to city delights, trendy café scenes and shopping strips. First home buyers, professional couples, down-sizers or the smart investor it will be difficult to pass on once you discover what this immaculate low maintenance modern villa has to offer.
The sun-drenched single level layout has been designed with a low-maintenance edge to deliver the ultimate carefree lifestyle, showcasing a truly sensational open plan living and meals area and modern updated kitchen, fitted with induction cook top and wall oven.
Two good-sized bedrooms, with built in mirrored robes, share the full central bathroom, equipped with both shower and bath and separate toilet for convenience.
The private courtyard, free of any grass, ensures you have all the time in the world and ample space to relax outdoors or fire up the BBQ for friends.
Gas wall heating, a single lock up garage with dual access to the home, plus additional car space are handy inclusions in this spacious sun-kissed villa unit, that's within easy reach of cosmopolitan Sydney Road's lifestyle delights, train stations and schools.

Description:
The Perfect Starter In Prime Location
With a wealth of period details and city convenience close by, this freestanding two bedroom single fronted original period style home makes for an enchanting lifestyle opportunity. A traditional layout, of central lounge, dining room and hallway, features leadlight aspects with open plan living and dining area followed by the kitchen located in the rear, this home offers a great sense of space and comfort. To add to this, two generous size bedrooms with open fire places and double glazed windows, ducted heating throughout and split system cooling. Everything you need is right here and all in a prime position that is a short stroll to Coburg Railway Station, Coburg North Village shopping precinct, Coburg North Primary School, Sydney Road shops and cafés, Farmer's Market, parks, and the Merri Creek bike trail. Inspections are sure to impress!
